![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/1577294203930-IQ3MOBQ31MWROTX07QZA/Episode36.jpg?format=original)

Superman is a DAD?! This week the guys at Comicbook Clique open up a whole jar of wholesome, as they gush over the greatness that is Superman Vol. 1 Son of Superman. Written by Peter J. Tomasi with art by Patrick Gleason, Son of Superman shows us Clark Kent as as dad of steel, teaching his son Jon the life lessons he learned as a kid from Smallvile. With touching dialogue, beautiful art and an appearance by Krypto the dog, Son of Superman is the cure for the common case of the blah and proves the only thing more powerful than Kryponite is family. 

If you can, please leave us a **_review_** on [**ITunes**](https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/major-issues-podcast/id1321720972) so we can grow our audience and grow as podcasters! Rate us where ever podcasts are found. Don't forget to check out our merchandise! All episodes of Major Issues are brought to you by **ComicBook Clique**, the one stop for the latest and greatest things to come to comic books and comic book media.  
  
